saveDrc(25.10)                                                  saveDrc(25.10)

Name
       saveDrc - Saves DRC violation markers in the specified file

Syntax
       saveDrc

       [-help]

       <fileName>[-force]

       [-selected]

       Saves  DRC violation markers in the specified file. The saveDrc command
       is useful for situations where you want to save DRC  violation  markers
       without having to save the entire design.

       For  example,  if  during ECO you find that only 25 of the 500 reported
       violations are actual violations that need to be corrected immediately,
       you can:

              * Delete the other 475 violations.

              * Save the 25 violations in a marker file using the saveDrc com-
                mand.

              * Clear the violations from the design window.

              * Load the marker file containing the  saved  violation  markers
                using the loadDrc command.

       Use  the  saveDrc command after markers have been flagged by any of the
       following commands:

              * verify_drc

              * verifyMetalDensity

       You can also use this command to save Calibre violation markers after a
       Calibre file has been loaded using the loadViolationReport command.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each saveDrc parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man saveDrc

       <fileName>
              Saves the DRC violation markers in a  file  with  the  specified
              name.

       -force Creates drc file with a 0 drc count.

              Note: When there is no drc in the design, drc file is not gener-
              ated (Default).

       -selected
              Saves only the selected DRC violation markers.

Examples
       The following command saves markers to the VG.drc file:

       saveDrc VG.drc

Related Information
              * verify_drc

              * The  following  sections in the Identifying and Viewing Viola-
                tions chapter of User Guide:

